videos.description: Defense is ruling the day early in the Famous Idaho Potato Bowl as Jayshawn Jordan jumps in front of the route and makes the pick for Idaho to stymie the Colorado State drive.
videos.headline: Jordan makes the pick to end Colorado State's drive

videos.description: After a scoreless first quarter, Colorado State only needs 25 seconds in the second quarter before Nick Stevens hits Olabisi Johnson for a 52-yard touchdown strike to give the Rams a 7-0 lead.
videos.headline: Colorado State strikes first with 52-yard TD

videos.headline: I. Saunders run for 2 yds for a TD

videos.description: Isaiah Saunders finds a hole and then needs to break two tackles before seeing nothing but open field in front of him for the 26-yard touchdown to put Idaho in front 13-7.
videos.headline: Saunders busts through the line for 26-yard Idaho TD

videos.description: Idaho finishes off an 18-play, 85-yard drive when Matt Linehan finds Jacob Sannon for the six-yard touchdown to put the Vandals up 20-7 just before halftime.
videos.headline: Idaho cashes in long drive for TD just before the half

videos.description: Idaho head coach Paul Petrino discusses team's 1st half performance
videos.headline: Idaho head coach Paul Petrino discusses team's 1st half performance

videos.headline: Colorado State head coach Mike Bobo talks about improvements needed for 2nd half

videos.description: When he can't find anyone open, Matt Linehan keeps it himself and scrambles into the end zone for Idaho's fourth straight drive scoring a touchdown, and boosting the Vandals' lead to 27-7.
videos.headline: Linehan scrambles in for Idaho's fourth straight TD

videos.description: Matt Linehan goes deep to Deon Watson for the catch and then turns on the jets to score Idaho's fifth touchdown in their last five possessions turning the game into a 34-7 rout.
videos.headline: Idaho can't stop scoring, this time with 74-yard TD
